                <note rend="inline" type="source">500.A15/450: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the Chief
                        of the American Representation on the Preparatory Commission</hi> (<persName
                        type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Gibson</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1927-03-25T17:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 25, 1927—5 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>98. Owing to late arrival of your telegrams on statement you propose to make, it
                    is impossible for me to examine matter carefully and advise you tonight. I
                    think, however, that in main it is too much an endorsement of League
                    supervision, as our argument has always been not only that such supervision
                    could not be accepted by us but that it is vicious in principle as its only
                    effect will be to create distrust and suspicion between nations. In addition I
                    do not think that we are justified in saying that we have no intention at
                    present of materially increasing our land forces. Your draft will be considered
                    and reply sent some time tomorrow.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Kellogg</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
